@startuml

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Segoe UI"
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam activityBackgroundColor #F8F9FA
skinparam activityBorderColor #495057
skinparam activityArrowColor #495057
skinparam activityFontColor #212529
skinparam partitionBackgroundColor #E9ECEF
skinparam partitionBorderColor #6C757D
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF9E6
skinparam noteBorderColor #C9A400

title Tracing Span and Trace Lifecycle

'──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
'  SECTION 1 — TRACE LIFECYCLE
'──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

|Caller / Runner|
start
:Enter trace context\n**with trace(workflow_name)**;

|TraceCtxManager|
:create_trace_for_run()\nworkflow_name, trace_id, group_id,\nmetadata, tracing, disabled;

if (Active trace already\npresent in Scope?) then (yes)
  :Return None\n(reuse existing trace context);
  stop
else (no)
endif

if (Resumed run &\nreattach_resumed_trace=True\n& trace_id already started?) then (yes)
  :reattach_trace()\nReturn **ReattachedTrace**;
  note right
    on_trace_start is NOT fired.
    Trace silently registered as
    current in Scope only.
  end note
else (no)
  |DefaultTraceProvider|
  :_refresh_disabled_flag()\nCheck OPENAI_AGENTS_DISABLE_TRACING\nenv var + manual override;

  if (Tracing disabled?) then (yes)
    :Return **NoOpTrace**;
    note right
      No processor callbacks fired.
      Scope context management
      still functions normally.
    end note
  else (no)
    :Create **TraceImpl**\n(trace_id, workflow_name, group_id,\nmetadata, processor=\nSynchronousMultiTracingProcessor);
  endif
endif

|TraceCtxManager|
:trace.start(mark_as_current=True);

|TraceImpl|
:Set _started = True\n_mark_trace_id_started(trace_id);

|SynchronousMultiTracingProcessor|
:**on_trace_start(trace)** — Fan-out;
fork
  :Processor 1\non_trace_start(trace);
fork again
  :Processor 2 … N\non_trace_start(trace);
end fork
note right
  Processors iterated in order.
  Exceptions caught & logged per
  processor — others still execute.
  Thread-safe: processors read
  from immutable snapshot tuple.
end note

|Scope (contextvars)|
:set_current_trace(TraceImpl)\n→ Token stored for later reset\n(async-safe via Python contextvar);

'──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
'  SECTION 2 — SPAN CREATION & LIFECYCLE
'──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

|Caller / Runner|
:WORKFLOW EXECUTES
----
Enter span context\n**with agent_span(...) as span**\n(also: generation_span, function_span,\nguardrail_span, handoff_span, custom_span…);

|DefaultTraceProvider|
:create_span(span_data, span_id, parent)\n_refresh_disabled_flag();

if (Tracing disabled?) then (yes)
  :Return **NoOpSpan**(span_data);
  note right
    NoOpSpan propagates when:
    • Global tracing is disabled
    • No current trace in Scope
    • Current trace is NoOpTrace
    • Parent span is NoOpSpan
  end note
else (no)
  if (No current trace\nin Scope?) then (yes)
    :Log error\nReturn **NoOpSpan**;
  else (no)
    if (Current trace is NoOpTrace\nor parent span is NoOpSpan?) then (yes)
      :Return **NoOpSpan**\n(propagate NoOp to child);
    else (no)
      :Resolve parent context:\n• parent=None → parent_id from\n  Scope.get_current_span()\n  trace_id from current_trace\n• parent=Trace → parent_id=None\n• parent=Span → parent_id=span.span_id;
      :Create **SpanImpl**\n(trace_id, span_id, parent_id,\nprocessor=SynchronousMultiTracingProcessor,\nspan_data, tracing_api_key);
    endif
  endif
endif

|SpanImpl|
:__enter__() → start(mark_as_current=True)\nSet _started_at = time_iso();

|SynchronousMultiTracingProcessor|
:**on_span_start(span)** — Fan-out;
fork
  :Processor 1\non_span_start(span);
fork again
  :Processor 2 … N\non_span_start(span);
end fork

|Scope (contextvars)|
:set_current_span(SpanImpl)\nNested spans auto-inherit parent_id\nvia Scope.get_current_span();

|Caller / Runner|
:OPERATION RUNS\n(nested spans created inside\nwith deeper parent_id nesting);

|SpanImpl|
:__exit__() → finish(reset_current=True)\nSet _ended_at = time_iso();
note right
  If GeneratorExit is raised,
  Scope reset is skipped
  (generator cleanup path).
end note

|SynchronousMultiTracingProcessor|
:**on_span_end(span)** — Fan-out;
fork
  :Processor 1\non_span_end(span);
fork again
  :Processor 2 … N\non_span_end(span);
end fork

|Scope (contextvars)|
:reset_current_span(_prev_span_token)\nRestores parent span as active;

'──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
'  SECTION 3 — TRACE TEARDOWN & EXPORT
'──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

|TraceCtxManager|
:trace.finish(reset_current=True);

|TraceImpl|
:Call _processor.on_trace_end(self);

|SynchronousMultiTracingProcessor|
:**on_trace_end(trace)** — Fan-out;
fork
  :Processor 1\non_trace_end(trace);
fork again
  :Processor 2 … N\non_trace_end(trace);
end fork

|Scope (contextvars)|
:reset_current_trace(token)\nRestores previous trace context;

|BatchTraceProcessor|
:Buffer spans & traces\nin in-memory queue;
:Export batches to\nOpenAI backend (BackendSpanExporter)\nevery few seconds or on queue fill;
note right
  Default processor registered at
  GLOBAL_TRACE_PROVIDER init (lazy).
  atexit hook ensures final flush
  on process exit.
  Call flush_traces() for immediate
  delivery in long-running workers
  (Celery, RQ, FastAPI tasks).
end note

|Caller / Runner|
stop

@enduml
